## 🧠 Decision Point Example (From v1.2 Upgrade Docs):
**Scenario:** After successful BFT consensus round, decide whether to inject probabilistic CPU overload or keep system running normally for testing resilience.

```typescript
// TypeScript Interface Effect from upgrade docs: State Mutation Contract  
{ type: 'FAILURE', nodeId?: string, reason?: 'CPU'|'MEM'|'DISK'}  

# Rust struct mutation via Arc<T> (zero-copy shallow clone) ready per Phase MVP deliverable specs  
struct FailNode { pub node_id: String, cause: FailureCause }
impl LabState { 
    pub fn inject_cpu_failure(&self, node_id: &str) -> Self {
        let mut state = self.state.clone();  // Arc<T> shallow clone for async context safety per v1.2 docs Section 4 State Mutation Contract  
        return state;    
}  
}  

# Example payload to inject CPU overload - simpleModeHint enabled per chapter config from Phase MVP deliverable requirements  
```

